g.text: 3b. Invalidate ALL entries matching VPN [Global ASID Scan]

div.p: Steps 3 4 5 must occur in this exact order.

ol.li: Flush TLB (3): Prevents hardware from using cached translation.
Clear PTE (4): Prevents future walks from finding the mapping.
Free Frame (5): Only safe once no stale pointers (TLB or PTE) exist.

p.em: Failure to flush before freeing frame allows a stale TLB entry to point to a reassigned frame, leading to silent memory corruption.
